<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8"/>
    <title>FUMO</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="pages/css/index.css" />
</head>

<body>
    <a href="https://github.com/Ununoctium117/fumosite">
        <img class="github-banner" src="img/forkimg.png" alt="Fork me on GitHub">
    </a>

    <h1>Helpful Japanese Phrases</h1>

    <table class="striped sticky">
        <caption>Keywords</caption>
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>English</th>
                <th class="left">Japanese (Most Common)</th>
                <th class="left">Japanese (Alt. Forms)</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            {{#japanese.keywords}}
                <tr>
                    <td>{{en}}</td>
                    <td class="left"><span class="jp">{{jp}}</span></td>
                    <td class="left">
                        {{#jp_alt}}
                            <span class="jp">{{.}}</span>
                        {{/jp_alt}}
                    </td>
                </tr>
            {{/japanese.keywords}}
        </tbody>
    </table>

    <p>
        Some online storefronts require you to enter your own name and will only accept Japanese characters.
        <a href="https://www.sljfaq.org/cgi/e2k.cgi">This site</a> can help - it will phonetically
        translate your name into katakana, one of the two Japanese syllabaries.
    </p>

    <table class="striped sticky">
        <caption>Form Fields</caption>
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>Japanese (Most Common)</th>
                <th>Japanese (Alt. Forms)</th>
                <th class="left">English</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            {{#japanese.form_elements}}
                <tr>
                    <td><span class="jp">{{jp}}</span></td>
                    <td>
                        {{#jp_alt}}
                            <span class="jp">{{.}}</span>
                        {{/jp_alt}}
                    </td>
                    <td class="left">{{en}}</td>
                </tr>
            {{/japanese.form_elements}}
        </tbody>
    </table>

    <p>
        Names are given in the original order ZUN used. For Japanese names like Hakurei Reimu, that
        means the family name comes first. For Western names like Alice Margatroid, the given name comes first.
    </p>
    <table class="striped sticky">
        <caption>Characters</caption>
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>English</th>
                <th class="left">Japanese (Most Common)</th>
                <th class="left">Japanese (Alt. Forms)</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            {{#japanese.characters}}
                <tr>
                    <td>{{en}}</td>
                    <td class="left"><span class="jp">{{jp}}</span></td>
                    <td class="left">
                        {{#jp_alt}}
                            <span class="jp">{{.}}</span>
                        {{/jp_alt}}
                    </td>
                </tr>
            {{/japanese.characters}}
        </tbody>
    </table>
</body>
</html>